import React, { useEffect, useState } from 'react'; import EventCard from '../components/EventCard'; import './EventsPage.css'; const TechnicalEventsPage: React.FC = () => { const [isLoaded, setIsLoaded] = useState(false); useEffect(() => { setIsLoaded(true); window.scrollTo(0, 0); }, []); // Technical events data const technicalEvents = [ { title: "PITCH4SUSTAIN", description: "A sustainability-focused hackathon where teams develop innovative solutions for environmental challenges.", venue: "002 Block", registrationFee: "₹500 per team", teamSize: "1-5 members", date: "MAR 27", image: "/images/posters/pitch4sustain.jpg", organizer: "Department of Computer Science", contact: "+91 8296019911", details: (

About the Event

PITCH4SUSTAIN is a 24-hour hackathon focused on developing innovative solutions for environmental sustainability. Participants will work in teams to create prototypes that address real-world environmental challenges.

Rules & Guidelines

  • Teams must consist of 1-5 members
  • All code must be written during the event
  • Solutions must address a sustainability challenge
  • Final presentations should be under 5 minutes
  • Judging based on innovation, feasibility, and impact

Prizes

  • 1st Prize: ₹10,000 + Certificates
  • 2nd Prize: ₹5,000 + Certificates
  • 3rd Prize: ₹3,000 + Certificates

About the Event

PHANTOM HUNT is an exciting treasure hunt that combines technical knowledge with problem-solving skills. Teams will navigate through a series of cryptic clues, coding challenges, and technical puzzles spread across the campus.

Rules & Guidelines

  • Teams must consist of 4-5 members
  • At least one mobile device with internet access is required
  • No external help is allowed during the hunt
  • Time-based scoring system
  • All team members must stay together throughout the hunt

Prizes

  • 1st Prize: ₹8,000 + Certificates
  • 2nd Prize: ₹4,000 + Certificates
  • 3rd Prize: ₹2,000 + Certificates

About the Event

DRONEXTREME is an exciting drone racing competition where teams navigate custom-built or modified drones through complex obstacle courses. Show off your piloting skills and technical modifications in this high-flying challenge!

Rules & Guidelines

  • Teams must bring their own drones (specifications provided upon registration)
  • Maximum drone dimensions: 30cm x 30cm x 15cm
  • Maximum weight: 500g
  • All drones must have a fail-safe mechanism
  • Racing will involve both speed and precision challenges

Prizes

  • 1st Prize: ₹12,000 + Certificates
  • 2nd Prize: ₹8,000 + Certificates
  • 3rd Prize: ₹4,000 + Certificates
) }, { title: "SYNTAX SCRAMBLE", description: "A coding competition that tests algorithmic thinking, problem-solving, and programming efficiency.", venue: "FET Computer Labs", registrationFee: "₹150 per person", teamSize: "Individual", date: "MAR 27", image: "/images/posters/syntax scramble.jpg", organizer: "Coding Club", contact: "+91 8296019911", details: (

About the Event

SYNTAX SCRAMBLE is an intense individual coding competition that challenges participants to solve algorithmic problems efficiently. Test your programming skills, logical thinking, and code optimization in this fast-paced contest.

Rules & Guidelines

  • Individual participation only
  • Programming languages allowed: C, C++, Java, Python
  • Three rounds: Qualification, Main Round, and Finals
  • Time limits will be strictly enforced
  • Internet access will be restricted during the contest

Prizes

  • 1st Prize: ₹5,000 + Certificate
  • 2nd Prize: ₹3,000 + Certificate
  • 3rd Prize: ₹1,500 + Certificate
) }, { title: "INNOVATHON", description: "An innovation marathon where teams develop prototypes to solve industry-specific challenges.", venue: "IIAME Innovation Hub", registrationFee: "₹300 per team", teamSize: "3-5 members", date: "MAR 27-28", image: "/images/posters/innovathon.jpg", organizer: "IIAME", contact: "+91 8296019911", details: (

About the Event

INNOVATHON brings together creative minds to develop innovative solutions for real industry problems. Teams will have 36 hours to conceptualize, design, and develop a working prototype that addresses specific challenges provided by industry partners.

Rules & Guidelines

  • Teams must have 3-5 members from any discipline
  • Challenges will be announced at the start of the event
  • Teams must develop a working prototype during the event
  • All necessary equipment should be brought by participants
  • Final presentations will be judged by industry experts

Prizes

  • 1st Prize: ₹15,000 + Internship Opportunities + Certificates
  • 2nd Prize: ₹8,000 + Certificates
  • 3rd Prize: ₹4,000 + Certificates

About the Event

MODEL BLITZ is an exhibition-style competition where participants showcase their engineering models, prototypes, and solutions to real-world problems. This event celebrates innovation and practical application of engineering principles.

Rules & Guidelines

  • Open to individuals or teams
  • Models must be original and developed by the participants
  • Exhibition space of 1.5m x 1m will be provided
  • Participants must bring all required materials
  • Models will be judged on innovation, design, functionality, and presentation

Prizes

  • 1st Prize: ₹7,000 + Certificates
  • 2nd Prize: ₹4,000 + Certificates
  • 3rd Prize: ₹2,000 + Certificates
  • People's Choice Award: ₹1,000 + Certificate
